<%# v7 app footer -- used by layouts/main.ejs (authenticated interior pages).
    3-column nav structure (Platform / Learn / Company) for orientation when
    you're deep in the app. Same dark slab and brand mark as the marketing
    v7-footer, just denser link grouping. The lighter marketing footer with
    the mascot peeking out stays on layouts/v7.ejs landings.

    Uses standard flex (no bracket-notation grid) so Tailwind's purge picks
    up every class. Mirrors the structure of the previous bg-otp-950 footer
    that worked, only re-skinned to v7 visual identity. %>
<footer class="bg-[#0c1626] text-[#aeb7c6] relative overflow-hidden">
  <img src="/public/orgy-clean.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true"
       class="pointer-events-none select-none absolute hidden lg:block"
       style="right:48px; bottom:-118px; width:212px; z-index:0; opacity:0.55;">
  <div class="max-w-[1180px] mx-auto px-6 pt-14 pb-12 relative" style="z-index:1;">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between gap-10">
      <div class="max-w-xs">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2.5">
